        <item>
          <title>Replace map tooltip with a refine : see the aggregation !</title>
          <link>https://codelibrary.opendatasoft.com/widget-tricks/ods-map-tricks/#replace-map-tooltip-with-a-refine--see-the-aggregation-</link>
          
            <pubDate>Wed, 30 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
          
          
          <guid>https://codelibrary.opendatasoft.com/widget-tricks/ods-map-tricks/#replace-map-tooltip-with-a-refine--see-the-aggregation-</guid>
          <description>&lt;p&gt;In this example, in combination with &lt;a href=&#34;https://codelibrary.opendatasoft.com/widget-tricks/ods-color-gradient/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ods-color-gradient&lt;/code&gt; to display a choropleth map&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;code&gt;refineOnClick&lt;/code&gt; is used to select a department and activate KPI cards on top of the map.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the first KPI card displays the aggregation result from &lt;code&gt;ods-color-gradient&lt;/code&gt; and display it&amp;rsquo;s value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the second KPI card get the name of the selected department, through an &lt;code&gt;ods-results&lt;/code&gt; on the refined context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the third KPI card computes a new aggregation with &lt;code&gt;ods-adv-analysis&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
        </item>
      
    
      
      
